				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Nope, I'm not in charge of it, I just called it mine because I designed the Squeedo mapper and board and asked for that # to be reserved years ago.<br /><br />The real limitation is with the iNES format specifying the size in 16kB banks.  The solution I would propose would be for an emulator to load as 8kB if the number of PRG banks is zero.  I don't know how well that proposal would go over.  Galaxian seems to be the only one like that.  But I seriously doubt anyone would make a cart that's smaller than that, so it seems like a possible solution.<br /><br />Better check iNES 2.0 too, to see if anything like that is specified in it.  It could already be, for all I know.</div>
<br />
<br />If I'm not mistaken, the extended header of iNES includes PRG ram bank
<br />infos stepping 8k-wise, not the rom which is still stepped 16k-wise. 
<br />Also, the clrMamePro's default header checker for NES doesn't provide 
<br />support for the extended headers that use 0008h ~ 000fh. You can check 
<br />this at &lt;clrmamepro dir&gt;\headers\nes.xml, if you have installed the 
<br />clrmamepro
<br />
<br />Surely changing the behavior of mapper 0 based on the PRG rom size 
<br />can be another way to solve the problem. But it would introduce some programming overhead for the mapper 0. 
<br />
<br />I still think it is more preferable to add an extra mapper for the Galaxian, 
<br />especially it is the only one of their kind. We have a lot of mappers to 
<br />spare, so why not waste them <img src="./images/smilies/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt=":roll:" title="Rolling Eyes" /></div>

