					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">kshin981 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Yes, it DOES require wiring, and you are still missing the point. In order for the mirroring to occur, the top most addresses need to be HARD-WIRED together. </div>
<br />
<br />That is a side effect of using the wrong hardware. If you had an 8kB ROM there would be no top-most address lines to need to connect.
<br />
<br />Since the current Galaxian rip falsely claims 16kB ROM, it comes pre-mirrored in the iNES file, and, in turn, if you just put that in a 16kB ROM it would also just work, without any hard-wiring of upper address lines.</div>

